Your runner role poc-runner-role needs these EC2 permissions added. Ask your AWS admin to attach this inline policy to poc-runner-role:

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "ec2:AssociateIamInstanceProfile",
        "ec2:ReplaceIamInstanceProfileAssociation",
        "ec2:DisassociateIamInstanceProfile",
        "ec2:DescribeIamInstanceProfileAssociations",
        "ec2:DescribeInstances",
        "iam:PassRole"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
Steps for your admin:

IAM → Roles → poc-runner-role
Add permissions → Create inline policy → JSON → paste above
Name it: allow-ec2-instance-profile-attach
Save
Without these permissions, the pipeline cannot attach the IAM role to your SAP HANA EC2 instances — which is a core requirement of your setup.

Alternatively, if you can't get this permission either, I can remove the ec2-role-attachment module and you'd attach the instance profile to each EC2 manually via AWS Console. Want me to do that?


